                <h5 class="group-header">Consortiums/Third Party Administrator (C/TPA)</h5>
                <div class="info-block-wrapper">
                    {{!-- <img src="assets/images/" ALIGN="left" /> --}}
                    <h2 class="more-info-text">Companies under the Department of Transportation regulations rule 49 CFR Part 40 are required to comply with federal requirements for random testing. We offer customized random pool programs based on DOT requirements. For larger companies a stand alone pool may be sufficient to ensure the appropriate frequency of testing for your employees.</h2>
                    <h2 class="more-info-text">For smaller companies, and Owner/Operators a national consortium pool is the best option. A national consortium ensures your employees are part of a random drug testing pool while providing the advantages of a larger pool size, including reducing the frequency of testing for smaller companies.</h2>
                    <h2 class="more-info-text">Additionally, if designated as your C/TPA in the DOT Clearinghouse we can assist with meeting your query and violation reporting requirements.</h2>
                    <h2 class="more-info-text">A Clearinghouse query is an electronic check to determine if current or prospective employees are prohibited from performing safety-sensitive functions, such as operating a commercial motor vehicle (CMV), due to unresolved drug and alcohol program violations.</h2>
                </div>

